19:34.006 --> 19:35.268
who are being tutored.

19:35.874 --> 19:37.705
Whoever did this will be expelled.

19:39.011 --> 19:40.342
Or worse.

19:51.790 --> 19:54.623
I will bet you anything
Rachel stole those tests.

19:54.693 --> 19:56.320
- What?
- When I was tutoring her,

19:56.395 --> 19:57.953
she tried to bribe me for them.

19:58.030 --> 20:00.191
Haley, I live with Rachel.

20:01.400 --> 20:03.391
If she'd stolen the tests, I'd know.

20:08.106 --> 20:11.007
Hey. We have a problem.

20:11.076 --> 20:14.045
Yeah, you stabbed me in the back
from the front.

20:14.112 --> 20:15.101
Okay, we have two problems.

20:15.180 --> 20:17.808
Did you return the calculus exams
that we stole?

20:17.883 --> 20:19.180
Maybe.

20:19.585 --> 20:21.519
- Okay, I forgot.
- Rachel!

20:21.587 --> 20:24.420
Turner knows the tests are missing,
and now he's on a total witch hunt.

20:24.489 --> 20:25.922
Who cares, Brooke?
He doesn't know it was us.

20:25.991 --> 20:27.754
The bigger problem
is how you left me hanging today.

20:28.627 --> 20:30.458
You said it yourself,
Clean Teens was our alibi.

20:30.529 --> 20:33.089
Otherwise, we can't justify
why we were in the school that night.

20:33.165 --> 20:34.393
That is not what's going on.

20:34.466 --> 20:36.764
You screwed me over for a guy
who won't screw you.

20:37.836 --> 20:43.035
Oh, please, like I couldn't get Chase
after a little chase.

20:44.109 --> 20:45.667
I think you're forgetting something.

20:45.744 --> 20:48.338
You see, Chase is into smart,
born-again-virgin Brooke,

20:48.413 --> 20:51.382
not stupid, slutty,
"I cheated on the calculus test" Brooke.

20:51.450 --> 20:53.145
Fine. But have you seen me?

20:53.218 --> 20:56.085
Because I could easily have sex
with him if I wanted to.

20:56.154 --> 20:58.782
Interesting. Care to bet on that?

21:01.493 --> 21:03.757
- Took you long enough.
- Dude, these outfits rock.

21:03.829 --> 21:05.922
You guys are gonna win
that $1,000 hands down.

21:05.998 --> 21:07.192
Or pants down.

21:07.266 --> 21:08.756
Hey, I don't know. I still suck.

21:08.834 --> 21:11.268
Look, man, we're going to be fine.
I just need you to look good.

21:11.336 --> 21:12.928
I'm gonna do all the dancing.

21:13.005 --> 21:14.632
- Let's see the outfits.
- Okay.

21:16.441 --> 21:17.908
Oh, yeah!

21:18.343 --> 21:19.605
Hell, no!

21:22.381 --> 21:23.473
He just playing, man.

21:23.548 --> 21:25.607
Look, I thought we'd go
with a different kind of uniform.

21:27.486 --> 21:28.783
Oh, okay.

21:31.490 --> 21:33.924
- All right.
- Dude, you should have seen your face.

21:37.663 --> 21:38.960
Peyton?

21:42.834 --> 21:44.426
I'm sorry.

21:47.172 --> 21:51.006
- Oh, this is messed up.
- Yeah, I know. The timer didn't go off.

21:51.076 --> 21:54.375
No, I mean,
like, I kind of expected it, you know?

21:54.446 --> 21:56.937
Like another day, another disaster.

21:57.516 --> 22:00.644
It's like with everything that's happened,
we've become chaos junkies.

22:02.954 --> 22:05.582
So, I told my mom about seeing Keith.

22:06.024 --> 22:09.653
I didn't even think about
how much it was gonna upset her.

22:10.128 --> 22:11.755
Luke, you didn't mean to hurt her.

22:11.830 --> 22:14.424
I know, but I did. You know, I just...

22:15.200 --> 22:18.431
I just want to let it all go away, you know?

22:18.503 --> 22:20.266
I don't want to be like this anymore.

22:23.408 --> 22:26.969
How'd you like to just be happy?

22:28.880 --> 22:30.905
I thought you'd never ask.

22:42.494 --> 22:45.088
It seems like I spend more time with Keith
now than I did when he was alive.

22:47.499 --> 22:50.263
- I'm sorry, I don't wanna intrude.
- Dan.

22:53.839 --> 22:54.999
I bought a roast for dinner,

22:55.073 --> 22:57.564
and I didn't know Lucas had plans tonight.

22:58.276 --> 22:59.834
It's gonna be too much for me.

23:01.279 --> 23:03.474
Would you like to come over for dinner?

23:03.949 --> 23:05.439
I'd like that.

23:17.162 --> 23:18.424
Oh, God.

23:20.065 --> 23:22.329
I thought vampires had to be invited in.

23:22.401 --> 23:25.370
And I thought water melted witches.
Yet, here we are.

23:26.037 --> 23:28.198
That was quite the performance
you put on today.

23:29.608 --> 23:33.567
Why are you messing with Karen's head?
Hasn't she suffered enough?

23:33.645 --> 23:36.136
You don't think my intentions
toward Karen are sincere?

23:36.214 --> 23:38.705
You don't have a sincere bone
in your body, Dan.

23:42.053 --> 23:43.918
Do you remember the night
before our wedding?

23:45.090 --> 23:46.216
You pour water in my face

23:46.291 --> 23:48.759
and now you want to take a trip
down memory lane?

23:57.602 --> 24:01.538
You disappeared after the rehearsal dinner
and my parents were furious.

24:02.140 --> 24:03.664
Is that what you wanted to hear?

24:04.709 --> 24:06.404
I drove to Tree Hill

24:08.213 --> 24:10.443
and spent the night parked
in front of Karen's house.

24:13.084 --> 24:15.780
I knew I was on the verge
of making a huge mistake.

24:18.390 --> 24:19.652
You see,

24:20.992 --> 24:22.721
Karen was the love of my life,

24:24.696 --> 24:26.493
yet I was too proud to tell her.

24:29.134 --> 24:30.999
I never loved you, Deb.

24:31.436 --> 24:33.199
I settled for you.

24:36.541 --> 24:39.169
And I mean that. Sincerely.

24:40.645 --> 24:43.011
You're a miserable ass of a man!

24:44.082 --> 24:48.610
Nathan and I are so much better off
without you poisoning our lives.

24:48.687 --> 24:51.485
Nathan and I? Take another pill, boozy.

24:51.556 --> 24:53.615
Nathan cut you out of his life
long before I did.

25:04.970 --> 25:05.959
Jeez.

25:06.304 --> 25:09.068
- Where's Nathan? I need to see him.
- Not like this, you don't.

25:09.140 --> 25:10.767
Don't keep me from my own son!

25:10.842 --> 25:13.276
Deb, you're the one ruining
your relationship with Nathan.

25:13.345 --> 25:14.403
Don't put that on me.

25:14.479 --> 25:16.242
I need to see him!

25:16.715 --> 25:17.739
Oh, God!

25:17.816 --> 25:18.908
Mom!

25:18.984 --> 25:22.181
Haley, are you okay? You all right?

25:22.254 --> 25:24.620
What are you doing?
She's pregnant, Mom!

25:24.689 --> 25:27.021
It was an accident.
I didn't mean to hurt her.

25:27.092 --> 25:29.458
Why don't you forget I exist
and we'll call it even, okay?

25:29.528 --> 25:30.756
- I'm sorry.
- No, Mom, you're leaving.

25:30.829 --> 25:33.992
And do not come back.
I'm not doing this anymore.

25:38.003 --> 25:39.698
You keep looking at me weird.

25:39.771 --> 25:41.636
I know. I'm sorry.

25:42.841 --> 25:45.833
It's just really hard for me to believe
that you've never had sex.

25:46.878 --> 25:48.470
It's not that I haven't had the opportunity.

25:49.114 --> 25:51.105
I just wanna wait
until I find the right person.

25:51.182 --> 25:53.241
But you've had girlfriends.

25:53.318 --> 25:58.051
I've had one serious girlfriend,
but it didn't end well.

25:58.557 --> 26:01.151
Did you break up
because she wanted to have sex?

26:01.226 --> 26:02.352
Yeah.

26:02.961 --> 26:04.326
With my best friend.

26:05.530 --> 26:08.693
Turns out she was cheating on me
pretty much the whole time.

26:08.767 --> 26:11.998
Wow, that... That sucks.

26:12.537 --> 26:17.236
Yeah, I lost my girlfriend
and my best friend on the same day.

26:17.776 --> 26:21.769
- I didn't know we had so much in common.
- That happened to you, too?

26:22.814 --> 26:24.111
They didn't have sex,

26:24.182 --> 26:28.619
but my best friend fell in love
with my boyfriend. Twice.

26:29.688 --> 26:33.055
- You guys still friends?
- Not like we used to be.

26:39.397 --> 26:42.389
I know people think
that being in Clean Teens is weird.

26:42.734 --> 26:44.634
I mean, especially being a guy.

26:45.003 --> 26:48.564
And, trust me,
it's not 'cause I don't love girls. I do,

26:49.407 --> 26:51.534
but I just wanted to start over, you know?

26:51.610 --> 26:56.104
I mean, the next relationship I get into
is gonna be with someone I can trust.

26:56.348 --> 26:58.077
Someone who's completely honest
with me.

27:07.292 --> 27:09.658
Mouth, you did not tell me
that Rachel and Bevin were coming.

27:09.728 --> 27:12.094
You guys need people cheering for you
if you wanna win,

27:12.163 --> 27:13.926
and who's better at cheering
than cheerleaders?

27:13.999 --> 27:17.662
- Please tell me you didn't invite Haley.
- I didn't invite Haley.

27:17.736 --> 27:21.172
But Skills told Peyton,
who might have told Lucas.

27:21.239 --> 27:22.365
So, there's that.

27:23.575 --> 27:24.803
Right.

27:28.046 --> 27:29.479
Coming!

27:29.714 --> 27:31.011
- Hey!
- Hi!

27:31.549 --> 27:32.538
- Turn around.
- Why?

27:32.617 --> 27:34.244
Get dressed. Luke's out in the car.
You're coming with us.

27:34.319 --> 27:36.116
Oh, no, no.
I really don't feel like going out tonight.

27:36.187 --> 27:37.415
Haley, where's your sense of adventure?

27:37.489 --> 27:39.719
It probably got knocked out of me
when I got hit by a car.

27:39.791 --> 27:42.157
Okay, well, seriously,
you're gonna want to see this.

27:42.227 --> 27:44.718
- Trust me, it'll be a night to remember. Go.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

27:50.502 --> 27:52.902
So, what do you think?
You ready to study?

27:52.971 --> 27:55.804
Oh, well, what else do you have in mind?

28:00.845 --> 28:02.403
We could dance.

28:02.981 --> 28:05.449
- Oh, no.
- Come on. Come on.

28:06.818 --> 28:09.252
I don't know how to dance
to this kind of music.

28:09.320 --> 28:11.311
It's easy. I'll show you.

28:17.095 --> 28:18.995
This isn't so bad, is it?

28:19.664 --> 28:21.427
It beats studying.

28:23.068 --> 28:26.435
My parents would dance like this,
you know, late at night after I went to bed.

28:26.504 --> 28:32.670
I used to sit at the top of the stairs
in my footie pajamas and just watch them.

28:34.045 --> 28:35.512
That was what? A year ago?

28:38.316 --> 28:40.978
They were so happy and so in love.

28:47.325 --> 28:50.158
- Your heart is beating really fast.
- Is it?

29:08.346 --> 29:10.177
That guy's gonna have a heart attack.

29:10.248 --> 29:13.217
I checked out all the other competition.
There's no way you guys don't win.

29:13.284 --> 29:15.149
Did you get a load of the guy
who looked like Chewbacca?

29:15.220 --> 29:17.085
Wait, I saw that guy! That dude is furry.

29:17.155 --> 29:18.918
Skills, check this out.

29:29.400 --> 29:32.096
Man, there's a lot of people out there.

29:33.605 --> 29:36.005
Man, is it hot in here or is it just me?

29:36.241 --> 29:38.607
Well, it's gonna be even hotter on stage
under those lights.

29:39.210 --> 29:40.438
Yeah?

30:16.114 --> 30:19.015
So tell me again why ice cream
was a good idea on a cold night?

30:19.083 --> 30:22.416
It's all part of my plan to get you cold
so I can warm you up.

30:24.355 --> 30:25.413
Pretty diabolical.

30:26.090 --> 30:28.957
That's what I do, Chase.
The boys can't resist my cuteness.

30:31.296 --> 30:33.321
I don't know if I'd call you cute.

30:33.431 --> 30:34.420
No?

30:34.966 --> 30:36.957
Nah. More like beautiful.

30:39.571 --> 30:41.163
Even with ice cream on your face.

30:42.774 --> 30:44.071
I got it.

30:53.318 --> 30:55.013
So tell me more about this plan.

30:55.253 --> 30:58.120
Skills, this plan was your idea.
What do you mean you can't go on?

30:58.189 --> 30:59.417
Man, you see all them people out there?

30:59.490 --> 31:02.084
Skills, you've played basketball
in front of thousands of people.

31:02.160 --> 31:04.219
Yeah, but they don't be all up on you
like that.

31:04.295 --> 31:06.195
Plus, I have my clothes on, man.

31:06.264 --> 31:08.824
<i>Our next act is Double Trouble!</i>

31:08.900 --> 31:10.458
That's us. What's it gonna be?

31:49.307 --> 31:52.276
Mama came to see her man dance
and her man's not on stage.

31:52.343 --> 31:55.073
Yeah, I know, baby,
but there's a whole lot of people out there.

31:55.146 --> 31:57.910
But if you don't dance for me,

31:58.516 --> 32:01.974
then you won't get to see me dance
for you.

32:54.872 --> 32:56.169
What happened to your stage fright?

32:56.240 --> 32:58.003
Mama came to see her man dance.

33:30.708 --> 33:32.437
Nathan looked good tonight.

33:32.510 --> 33:34.239
- No wonder you're pregnant.
- Oh, you're funny.

33:34.312 --> 33:36.371
- How's calculus going?
- Fine. Why?

33:36.748 --> 33:39.512
I just think it's wild
how you went from failing to fine

33:39.584 --> 33:41.074
with just a few tutoring sessions.

33:41.753 --> 33:44.187
You're just good, I guess.
Anyway, see you.

33:44.255 --> 33:46.917
Rachel, someone stole some tests
from the Tutoring Center

33:46.991 --> 33:50.324
and if I find out that it's you,
I'm turning you in.

34:02.106 --> 34:04.165
Is this important?
I'm running over to Karen's for dinner.

34:04.308 --> 34:06.708
I messed up so many things.

34:07.845 --> 34:09.710
Things I can't fix.

34:10.014 --> 34:13.040
How long is this gonna take?
I'm running low on minutes this month.

34:13.551 --> 34:15.518
<i>Please be good to Nathan.</i>

34:16.920 --> 34:19.856
I've failed him too many times to count.

34:21.125 --> 34:22.786
He deserves so much better.

34:23.027 --> 34:25.393
Deb, you gotta stop taking those pills.

34:25.463 --> 34:27.431
<i>It's all right now.</i>

34:29.434 --> 34:31.094
They're all gone.

34:35.739 --> 34:36.831
Deb?

34:37.909 --> 34:39.001
Deb?

34:50.353 --> 34:52.914
Karen, I'm sorry. I'm running late.
I should have called you.

34:54.225 --> 34:55.590
No, nothing important.

35:19.217 --> 35:20.946
Whoa, where'd you go?

35:21.018 --> 35:24.249
Well, this is one of the most notorious
make-out spots in town.

35:25.356 --> 35:28.120
It also has one of the nicest views in town.

35:28.192 --> 35:29.216
There's a view?

35:31.629 --> 35:32.618
Who knew?

35:36.767 --> 35:38.132
I thought maybe we could talk.

35:38.202 --> 35:39.191
Okay.

35:49.247 --> 35:52.648
Sorry, I haven't been a Clean Teen
very long.

35:53.351 --> 35:54.579
I know.

35:55.386 --> 35:57.445
I've seen your time capsule video.

35:57.822 --> 35:59.483
You don't see too many topless virgins.

36:01.058 --> 36:02.719
I can't believe you've seen that.

36:07.165 --> 36:09.861
I don't care about who you were, Brooke.

36:10.368 --> 36:11.835
I care about who you are.

36:13.738 --> 36:15.968
I didn't think guys like you
actually existed.

36:16.941 --> 36:20.240
Sweet and sincere and hot.

36:21.646 --> 36:22.977
You're like a unicorn.

36:24.715 --> 36:26.580
- A unicorn, huh?
- Yeah.

36:27.118 --> 36:30.918
How about a dragon?
Yeah, a dragon sounds way cooler.

36:33.124 --> 36:36.116
Okay. Yeah, you can be the dragon.

36:49.140 --> 36:52.166
What, too hot? What? What?

36:54.512 --> 36:57.276
- A little salty.
- Salty?

36:57.348 --> 37:00.408
I put a dash of salt in there.
That's what it said to do on the recipe.

37:01.018 --> 37:03.145
How much is a dash? Show me.

37:06.958 --> 37:10.018
Oh, that's... That's more like a handful.

37:10.528 --> 37:11.995
Oh, my God!

37:13.831 --> 37:16.459
Okay, great.
Well, maybe this batch will be better.

37:17.602 --> 37:18.591
Try it out.

37:23.841 --> 37:26.776
No. Still salty.

37:26.844 --> 37:29.108
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

37:29.180 --> 37:31.011
You know what?
Maybe I need a second opinion.

37:31.082 --> 37:33.312
- No!
- Oh, you better run!

37:39.857 --> 37:41.882
How you doing, hot stuff?

37:43.794 --> 37:45.887
Very funny. Get it all out.

37:46.264 --> 37:48.027
How much for a lap dance?

37:48.332 --> 37:49.356
You done?

37:49.433 --> 37:53.028
Not even close. I'm serious.
How much for a lap dance?

37:53.104 --> 37:54.401
I needed some quick cash, okay?

37:54.472 --> 37:55.598
What for?

37:56.173 --> 37:57.162
This.

38:02.713 --> 38:06.342
They actually have prom dresses
in the maternity section. Who knew?

38:06.417 --> 38:10.877
Nathan, this is really beautiful.

38:10.955 --> 38:12.582
Well, I'm just glad that we won tonight.

38:12.657 --> 38:14.818
Otherwise, I would have
had to take that back.

38:14.892 --> 38:16.985
I just wanted you
to have a great prom, Hales.

38:17.061 --> 38:19.393
Whoa! Thank you.

38:20.665 --> 38:22.360
Maybe we should have waited
to save the money

38:22.433 --> 38:23.525
until after you got a job.

38:23.601 --> 38:24.727
I'll get a job.

38:26.237 --> 38:28.865
You said, in a perfect world,
you'd wear a pretty dress

38:28.939 --> 38:30.497
and you'd dance with the man you love.

38:31.309 --> 38:33.243
Well, I don't think I'm gonna be dancing.

38:33.311 --> 38:35.541
I mean, you know,
the doctor said it takes most people...

38:35.613 --> 38:37.376
You're not most people.

38:37.448 --> 38:40.008
I've seen how you are
when you set your mind to something.

38:40.084 --> 38:42.678
You can do this. I'll help you.

38:55.132 --> 39:00.035
I had a really great time,
but I feel bad we didn't actually study.

39:02.406 --> 39:05.136
Maybe we could try again tomorrow night.

39:06.610 --> 39:08.373
Yeah, I'd like that.

39:10.247 --> 39:14.081
- Looks like your diabolical plan is working.
- Well...

39:40.544 --> 39:44.503
Okay. That was amazing.

39:45.082 --> 39:47.949
Well, when all you do is kiss,
you kind of get good at it.

39:48.419 --> 39:49.545
Yeah.

40:01.832 --> 40:04.960
Oh, man,
I've got cookie dough all over me.

40:05.069 --> 40:08.095
It's even in my bra.
Maybe I should take it off.

40:08.172 --> 40:09.400
What...

40:09.473 --> 40:10.701
Sucker!

40:12.443 --> 40:13.501
You surrender?

40:14.178 --> 40:17.079
I give up. I'm putting the lid down.

40:19.383 --> 40:21.408
Now if you are gonna
be taking anything off,

40:21.485 --> 40:24.750
please, please, please, let me help you.

40:28.159 --> 40:30.491
<i>Happiness comes in many forms.</i>

40:31.095 --> 40:33.393
<i>In the company of good friends,</i>

40:35.332 --> 40:38.893
<i>in the feeling you get when you make</i>
<i>someone else's dream come true,</i>

40:47.511 --> 40:49.945
<i>or in the promise of hope renewed.</i>

40:53.617 --> 40:55.983
You know what?
I think you missed some right there.

40:56.053 --> 40:57.350
Really?

41:03.527 --> 41:05.358
You know what? I take that back.

41:05.429 --> 41:08.557
- This is the best cookie I've ever had.
- Really?

41:14.572 --> 41:17.063
<i>It's okay to let yourself be happy.</i>

41:20.511 --> 41:23.605
- You've been quiet all night.
- I'm sorry.

41:24.815 --> 41:27.841
It's just that Lucas said
something really unsettling today.

41:28.552 --> 41:29.678
What'd he say?

41:30.654 --> 41:34.249
He said he doesn't think
that Jimmy Edwards killed Keith.

41:34.959 --> 41:37.985
<i>Because you never know</i>
<i>how fleeting that happiness might be.</i>

41:38.062 --> 41:39.188
Is that right?

42:13.898 --> 42:14.887
English

